  "bio": {
    "paragraphs": [
      "Hi there üëã I am a Senior Research Scientist at Google DeepMind, working on post-training for Gemini models. I have been a core contributor to the Google Gemini (1.5, 2.0, 2.5, and 3.0) launche series, specifically focusing on making Gemini the top-performing model for coding and WebApp development. We recently hit #1 on the WebDev Arena and Design Arena with the Gemini 3 launch! üöÄ ",
      "I completed my Ph.D. at USC, where I was honored as a 2023 EECS Rising Star and supported by an Amazon ML PhD Fellowship. My mentors were Xuezhe Ma and Nanyun Violet Peng. Over the years, my research has received some wonderful recognition, including a Best Paper Award at CVPR 2024, an Honorable Mention at CHI 2022 (as the first author), and an Honorable Mention at ACL 2021 (as the first author). ",
      "I am also deeply committed to AI education and outreach. I have had the pleasure of lecturing at the first Armenian Summer School on LLMs and being featured in a research profile by Amazon Science. Before USC, I was at IIIS, Tsinghua University, working with Dr. Wei Xu on AutoML."
    ],
